.TH HERMES 1 "2026-05-24" "WuBu Hermes Agent" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hermes, slermes \- AI agent CLI for conversation, tool execution, and gateway messaging
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hermes
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fImessage\fR]
.P
.B hermes \-\-gateway \-\-platform
.I platform
.SH DESCRIPTION
Hermes is an AI agent that runs local LLM inference or connects to
remote providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, DeepSeek, xAI, etc.) for conversation,
tool execution, and gateway messaging across 19 platforms.
.P
The first positional argument is treated as a one-shot message for
non-interactive use. Without arguments, Hermes starts in interactive
CLI mode with slash commands.
.P
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-tui
Launch full-screen terminal UI (requires ncurses).
.TP
.B \-\-gateway
Start gateway daemon for multi-platform messaging.
.TP
.B \-\-platform \fIplatform\fR
Platform to operate on (telegram, discord, slack, etc.). Used with \-\-gateway.
.TP
.B \-\-model \fImodel\fR
Override the LLM model.
.TP
.B \-\-provider \fIprovider\fR
Override the LLM provider.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output.
.TP
.B \-\-save-trajectory
Save conversation trajectory to file.
.TP
.B \-y, \-\-yes
Auto-approve all tool calls.
.SH SLASH COMMANDS
Interactive mode slash commands:
.P
.in +4n
.B /help
\(em Display command help.
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /status
\(em Session status (model, tokens, context, costs).
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /goal
\(em Save/show/clear session goal.
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /model
\(em Show or switch model.
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /provider
\(em Show or switch provider.
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /session
\(em Session management (list, search, export).
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /memory
\(em View or search memory.
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /config
\(em View or change configuration.
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /plugins
\(em List and manage plugins.
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /skills
\(em List, search, install skills.
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /browser
\(em Connect/disconnect CDP browser.
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /cron
\(em Schedule and list cron jobs.
.in -4n
.P
.in +4n
.B /completions
\(em Generate shell completion scripts.
.in -4n
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration directory: \fB$SLERMES_HOME\fR (default: \fB~/.slermes/\fR)
.TP
\fBconfig.yaml\fR
YAML config: provider, model, tools, gateway, plugins, etc.
.TP
\fB.env\fR
API keys and secrets (KEY=VALUE format).
.TP
\fBprofiles/\fR
Named config profiles (\fIprofile\fR.yaml), switched via \fB/config profile\fR.
.SH PLUGINS
Plugins load from \fB~/.hermes/plugins/\fR as .so files. Built-in plugins:
.IP \(bu 2
honcho-memory \(em In-memory memory backend (27-test verified)
.IP \(bu 2
kanban-board \(em Multi-agent task board (45-test verified)
.IP \(bu 2
spotify-control \(em Spotify Web API integration (18-test verified)
.SH GATEWAY PLATFORMS
Hermes supports messaging on 19 platforms:
telegram, discord, slack, matrix, mattermost, whatsapp, signal,
email, sms, webhook, homeassistant, dingtalk, wecom, weixin,
feishu, qqbot, bluebubbles, yuanbao, api_server.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBSLERMES_HOME\fR
Config directory path (default: ~/.slermes/).
.TP
\fBCAMOFOX_WS_URL\fR, \fBCHROME_WS_URL\fR
CDP WebSocket URL for browser automation.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
General error.
.TP
139
Segmentation fault (CUDA/GPU-related on release builds).
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.slermes/config.yaml\fR
User configuration.
.TP
\fI~/.slermes/.env\fR
Environment variables (API keys).
.TP
\fI~/.slermes/logs/\fR
Log files: agent.log, errors.log, gateway.log.
